South Africa Not Pushing Mine Nationalization, City Press Says

-- B y   N i c k y   S m i t h
-- 
2011-02-13T15:15:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-13/south-africa-not-pushing-mine-nationalization-city-press-says.html
South African President  Jacob Zuma 
said the government’s decision to establish a state mining
company and push for more domestic processing of raw commodities
don’t mean it plans to nationalize mining assets,  City Press 
reported.  Zuma said in an interview with the Johannesburg-based
newspaper that the government is talking to mining companies
about the proposals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicky Smith in Johannesburg at 
 nsmith38@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net . 